<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40169a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40169a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40169a"> 169(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Philadelphus </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Ptolemy II Philadelphus (Ptolemy Beloved of his Sibling), 309-246 BCE, was the king of Ptolemaic Egypt from 283 to 246 BCE. He was the son of the founder of the Ptolemaic kingdom Ptolemy I Soter and Berenice, and was educated by Philitas of Cos. He began his reign as co-regent with his father Ptolemy I from c. 285 BCE to c. 283 BCE, and maintained a splendid court in Alexandria. Egypt was involved in several wars during his reign. </mm> </dd></dl>
